		{
			"img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Reaction.webp",
			"name": "Nimble Dodge (Special)",
			"system": {
				"actionType": {
					"value": "reaction"
				},
				"actions": {
					"value": null
				},
				"category": "defensive",
				"description": {
					"value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A creature targets you with an attack and you can see the attacker or before you make a reflex save.</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong> You are not encumbered</p><hr><p>You deftly dodge out of the way, gaining a +2 circumstance bonus to AC against the triggering attack or a +2 circumstance bonus to the reflex save against the triggering effect.</p><p>In addition it also has the following effects:</p><ul><li><p><span style=\"font-family:Roboto, sans-serif\">When you use Nimble Dodge and the triggering attack fails or critically fails, or when you succeed or critically succeed at the saving throw, you can also roll, allowing you to Stride up to 10 feet as part of the reaction. If you do, the reaction gains the move trait. You can use this while Flying or Swimming instead of Striding if you have the corresponding movement type.</span></p></li><li><p>You can also make a melee strike against the triggering creature. <span style=\"font-family:Roboto, sans-serif\">This Strike doesn't count toward your multiple attack penalty, and your multiple attack penalty doesn't apply to this Strike. You can make the strike at any point during your roll.</span></p></li></ul>",
					"gm": ""
				},
